name: NPR
text:
As much as 95% of Kaziranga National Park in India may be underwater, following severe rain and flooding.

Now, officials are working to save stranded animals — including the area's rare one-horned rhinos.
https://t.co/0TyY63v69D

name: NPR
text:
The launch of the James Webb Space Telescope — the long-awaited successor to the Hubble Space Telescope — has been pushed back yet another seven months, NASA says.
https://t.co/gUUSCBewk5

name: NPR
text:
2020 has been a lot — and Iceland is ready to help.

The tourist board has developed an app that lets you record a scream, pent up by the pandemic, then broadcasts it from speakers in the Icelandic wilderness.
https://t.co/hvhJrhv80l

text:

name: NPR
text:
A spike in coronavirus cases in Colombia has forced many cities to issue new lockdown orders.  

Some people have turned to looting in order to survive — one scramble to steal gasoline ended in a hellish fireball.
https://t.co/iSMfrhggSb
